WEBVTT

00:00.757 --> 00:03.576
Last season on
Witches of East End...
BOTH: Mom!

00:03.609 --> 00:06.409
Girls, I want you
to meet your Aunt Wendy.

00:06.442 --> 00:08.042
Hi.
Freya...

00:08.075 --> 00:10.009
The girls don't
know what they are.

00:10.042 --> 00:12.909
I decided this life, for
once, they'd be normal.

00:12.942 --> 00:15.442
I need to tell you, it's the
truth about who we are.

00:15.475 --> 00:16.675
INGRID:
Please don't tell me...

00:16.709 --> 00:18.109
BOTH:
We're witches.

00:18.142 --> 00:21.242
All of our kind must abide,
we never reveal ourselves.

00:21.275 --> 00:22.909
What do you think the girls
are going to say

00:22.942 --> 00:25.275
when I tell them that you left
their brother behind?

00:25.309 --> 00:27.509
Victor!
It's really you.

00:27.542 --> 00:29.109
Who is this?
He's your father.

00:29.142 --> 00:31.009
Killian?
Well, I figured,
my big brother's

00:31.042 --> 00:32.175
getting married,
I should come congratulate him.

00:32.209 --> 00:33.942
I can't wait
to call you my wife.

00:33.975 --> 00:36.775
I'm in love with you.
I'm marrying Dash tomorrow.

00:36.809 --> 00:38.242
JOANNA:
One man is our soul mate,

00:38.275 --> 00:39.375
the other man's your destroyer.

00:39.409 --> 00:41.342
Killian left it.

00:41.375 --> 00:42.542
I can't marry you.

00:42.575 --> 00:44.609
Get out!
(Joanna screams)

00:44.642 --> 00:46.675
PENELOPE:
The argenteum has
taken its toll.

00:46.709 --> 00:48.742
Dash isn't really your son?
Oh, he is.

00:48.775 --> 00:50.042
I just borrowed
(screams)

00:50.075 --> 00:51.542
his powers
when he was a baby.

00:51.575 --> 00:53.242
(gasps)
And Killian's, too.

00:53.275 --> 00:54.809
(screams, grunts)

00:57.142 --> 00:59.475
Killian!

01:00.742 --> 01:02.375
Did she poison you
with argenteum?

01:02.409 --> 01:05.109
Yeah. I might not
have long left. (laughs)

01:05.142 --> 01:07.109
I want to know about Asgard.

01:07.142 --> 01:08.575
What happened there?

01:08.609 --> 01:10.175
There was a war...

01:10.209 --> 01:12.075
and we lost.

01:12.109 --> 01:15.542
If you could open the door
and go back... would you?

01:15.575 --> 01:17.309
I'd be pretty scared
to open that door.

01:18.375 --> 01:20.609
(man screaming)

01:42.575 --> 01:44.975
♪ ♪

01:55.375 --> 01:57.442
(rampant scampering away)

02:05.775 --> 02:08.075
(chopping)

02:08.109 --> 02:09.475
(herbs rustling)

02:15.142 --> 02:17.542
(inhales)

02:19.442 --> 02:23.742
Lumen eorum memoria.

02:23.775 --> 02:25.909
Lumen eorum
memoria.

02:25.942 --> 02:28.775
Lumen eorum memoria.

02:28.809 --> 02:30.509
Lumen eorum memoria.
(panting)

02:30.542 --> 02:32.609
(grunts)

02:32.642 --> 02:34.109
(Joanna moans)

02:34.142 --> 02:36.442
(Victor grunts)

02:36.475 --> 02:37.942
Do you trust me?

02:44.475 --> 02:46.475
(sighs)

02:56.542 --> 02:57.509
(moans)

02:57.542 --> 02:59.542
(sighs)

03:02.742 --> 03:03.909
(screaming, groaning)

03:03.942 --> 03:05.242
(grunting)

03:05.275 --> 03:07.275
(Joanna screams)

03:32.575 --> 03:35.542
(crickets chirping in distance)

03:52.475 --> 03:54.309
♪ ♪

04:08.275 --> 04:09.775
Has it been a week?

04:09.809 --> 04:12.275
I can't keep doing this,
it hurts too much.

04:12.309 --> 04:13.842
Until we find a cure for

04:13.875 --> 04:15.909
the argenteum poisoning...
these treatments

04:15.942 --> 04:17.375
are the only thing
keeping you alive.

04:18.475 --> 04:19.809
(screams, shrill groaning)

04:21.542 --> 04:22.675
(grunts)

04:22.709 --> 04:25.542
(screaming)

04:29.809 --> 04:31.409
(grunts)

04:31.442 --> 04:33.542
No...!
Hang in there, sweetheart.

04:33.575 --> 04:36.509
(groans, grunts, panting)
VICTOR: Hang in there.
Hang in there.

04:36.542 --> 04:39.542
You're doing great.
We're almost done.
(groaning)

04:39.575 --> 04:41.409
(yells)
(grunts)

04:41.442 --> 04:43.775
(Joanna screaming)

04:45.742 --> 04:47.509
I hate it when
she screams like that.

04:47.542 --> 04:49.942
Wendy says, that's a good sign.

04:49.975 --> 04:51.509
It means, she's
fighting for her life.

04:51.542 --> 04:53.275
And we should worry
when she stops screaming.

04:53.309 --> 04:54.909
(sighs)

04:54.942 --> 04:56.242
So, what are you doing up?

04:56.275 --> 04:58.909
I just woke up
in the front yard

04:58.942 --> 05:01.209
and I have no idea
how I got there.

05:01.242 --> 05:03.175
Isn't that, like,
the third time this week?

05:03.209 --> 05:06.242
I guess sleepwalking
is my new thing.

05:06.275 --> 05:08.742
Well, at least
you're sleeping. (sighs)

05:08.775 --> 05:10.042
I've barely gotten
more than an hour

05:10.075 --> 05:11.375
since the wedding.

05:11.409 --> 05:12.575
Oh. Freya, still?

05:12.609 --> 05:14.409
I swear, I didn't think
it was possible

05:14.442 --> 05:15.942
to screw up my life
this bad.

05:15.975 --> 05:18.075
Hey, Killian could come back.
You never know.

05:18.109 --> 05:19.542
No.

05:19.575 --> 05:21.009
He hasn't
returned my calls.

05:21.042 --> 05:23.142
My texts, my e‐mails.

05:24.642 --> 05:26.842
I think I just
need to let it go.

05:26.875 --> 05:29.509
Freya, I'm so sorry.

05:29.542 --> 05:30.609
Well...
(panting)

05:30.642 --> 05:31.609
I was right.

05:31.642 --> 05:32.942
What happened?
What do you mean?

05:32.975 --> 05:34.675
I knew something
came through the portal.

05:34.709 --> 05:35.875
What‐what do you mean?
You saw something?

05:35.909 --> 05:37.775
I may not remember
what happened that night...

05:37.809 --> 05:39.575
but I know someone
came through.

05:39.609 --> 05:40.742
I can sense him,

05:40.775 --> 05:42.275
hear him, smell him.

05:42.309 --> 05:43.609
I tracked him
to the forest tonight.

05:43.642 --> 05:45.209
I finally saw the
son of a bitch.

05:45.242 --> 05:46.742
What did he look like?!
You saw him?!

05:46.775 --> 05:48.409
He's cloaking himself, somehow.

05:48.442 --> 05:51.175
He moves really fast,
like a blur or a shadow.

05:51.209 --> 05:52.742
I can see his aura.
(closes refrigerator door)

05:52.775 --> 05:55.575
He's dark, evil,
predatory, hungry.

05:55.609 --> 05:56.609
He's messing with me

05:56.642 --> 05:59.175
like a cat, right before
it goes in for the kill.

05:59.209 --> 06:00.242
I guess, you would know.

06:00.275 --> 06:01.242
Yeah.
(sighs)

06:01.275 --> 06:03.042
Oh, good.
Another memory potion?
Yeah.

06:03.075 --> 06:04.209
We have to
remember what happened,

06:04.242 --> 06:05.442
before we
reseal the portal.

06:05.475 --> 06:07.509
We need to know
who we're dealing with.

06:07.542 --> 06:09.875
There's a reason he doesn't
want us to know who he is.

06:22.042 --> 06:24.675
(grunts)

06:24.709 --> 06:26.109
(exhales)

06:27.409 --> 06:29.809
(grunting)

06:30.909 --> 06:33.709
KILLIAN (distantly):
Dash...

06:37.109 --> 06:38.509
(echoing):
I've a bit of a headache.

06:38.542 --> 06:41.209
Want to take a look
at it for me? Doc?

06:41.242 --> 06:45.109
No. No, no.
You're not really here.

06:45.142 --> 06:46.609
You're a figment
of my imagination.

06:46.642 --> 06:48.442
I'm your conscience.

06:48.475 --> 06:50.709
It's frustrating,
isn't it?

06:50.742 --> 06:53.542
'Cause you can't recreate
what you did to me that night?

06:53.575 --> 06:56.042
It's driving you crazy,
literally, look at you.

06:56.075 --> 06:57.442
You're hallucinating.

06:58.909 --> 07:00.342
Of course,
the real question isn't

07:00.375 --> 07:01.775
how did you do it?

07:01.809 --> 07:04.109
(panting)
It's how can you
live with yourself?

07:04.142 --> 07:05.442
(strikes match)

07:06.742 --> 07:07.709
You murdered...

07:07.742 --> 07:09.242
your own...

07:09.275 --> 07:12.209
brother.
I didn't murder you!

07:12.242 --> 07:14.242
But I hope you're dead.

07:14.275 --> 07:16.542
You and Freya can rot...

07:16.575 --> 07:17.842
for all I care.

07:17.875 --> 07:19.575
You both deserve
whatever you get!

07:43.875 --> 07:45.509
Good idea, Freya.

07:45.542 --> 07:46.742
You really
should be resting.

07:46.775 --> 07:48.909
I'm fine.
You're not fine,

07:48.942 --> 07:50.709
I don't like you
pushing yourself.

07:50.742 --> 07:52.575
Since when
do you nag me?

07:52.609 --> 07:55.275
You don't have the luxury
of being reborn, Joanna.

07:55.309 --> 07:56.842
Neither do you,
anymore.

07:56.875 --> 07:58.742
But I don't have
a deadly poison

07:58.775 --> 08:00.842
weakening every organ
in my body.
(sighs)

08:00.875 --> 08:02.275
Freya did say this was
her strongest one yet,

08:02.309 --> 08:04.275
It is.
so maybe we should
try it first.

08:04.309 --> 08:06.875
Yeah.
Stop treating me,
like I'm made of glass.

08:06.909 --> 08:10.009
Victor and I have my condition
well under control.

08:10.042 --> 08:13.742
And I don't need the woman
who died in a trapeze accident

08:13.775 --> 08:15.342
lecturing me on safety.

08:15.375 --> 08:16.909
I died in a
trapeze accident?

08:16.942 --> 08:18.575
No. I did.
(laughs)

08:18.609 --> 08:20.275
Like you would ever
get on a trapeze.

08:20.309 --> 08:21.942
I might.
WENDY (laughing):
No, you wouldn't.

08:21.975 --> 08:23.175
You wouldn't even get on the
swings when we were kids.

08:23.209 --> 08:25.409
Hey, I can be
fearless and bold.

08:25.442 --> 08:26.875
JOANNA:
And thoughtful and cautious

08:26.909 --> 08:28.542
and there's nothing
wrong with that.

08:28.575 --> 08:30.909
I love that you're
someone we can count on.

08:30.942 --> 08:32.875
Reliable, always
here, no matter what,

08:32.909 --> 08:34.242
you're like an anchor.

08:34.275 --> 08:37.242
Okay. Come on.
Let's drink up.

08:37.275 --> 08:39.209
(inhales)
Cheers.
(sighs)

08:39.242 --> 08:40.875
Sláinte.

08:40.909 --> 08:42.542
Memories.

08:42.575 --> 08:44.242
FREYA:
Aperi... memoriae.

08:44.275 --> 08:46.075
Aperi memoriae.

08:46.109 --> 08:49.075
Aperi memoriae.

